SIMPLE: sometime
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Sometime
<hw>Some"time`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>adv.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>At a
past time indefinitely referred to; once; formerly.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Did they not <qex>sometime</qex> cry ⟦ldquo⟧All hail⟦rdquo⟧ to
me?</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>At a time undefined; once in a while; now and then;
sometimes.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Sometime</qex> we see a cloud that's dragonish,⟦br⟧
A vapor <qex>sometime</qex> like a bear or lion.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>At one time or other hereafter; <as>as, I will do it
<ex>sometime</ex></as>.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Sometime</xex> he reckon
shall.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1371 pr=RH --></p>

<p><ent>Sometime</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Sometime
<hw>Some"time`</hw> <pr>(s⟦ucr⟧m"t⟦imac⟧m`)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<def>Having been formerly; former; late; whilom.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Our <qex>sometime</qex> sister, now our queen.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Ion, our <qex>sometime</qex> darling, whom we prized.</q>
<rj><qau>Talfourd.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sometimes</ent>⟦br⟧
